# Implementation Plan - Phase 4: Shopping Cart and Checkout with Stripe Payment

We will implement a complete checkout flow. This includes global shopping cart state management using `useReducer`, a cart review page, backend database schemas for orders, a payment endpoint integrating Stripe Checkout sessions, and custom success/failed landing pages.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Components

We will create the database order models, checkout session controller endpoints, and payment routes.

#### [NEW] [Order.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/models/Order.js)
Defines the Mongoose order schema, capturing items bought, totalPrice, paymentResult logs, and delivery timestamps.

#### [NEW] [orderController.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/controllers/orderController.js)
Handles order database writes:
- `createOrder`: Creates a new order in MongoDB.
- `getOrderById`: Fetches an order by its ID.
- `getMyOrders`: Returns the active user's past order list.

#### [NEW] [paymentController.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/controllers/paymentController.js)
Integrates Stripe SDK:
- `createCheckoutSession`: Receives cart items, maps them to Stripe line items, creates a hosted checkout session, and returns the session URL.

#### [NEW] [orderRoutes.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/routes/orderRoutes.js)
Exposes endpoints for orders:
- `POST /api/orders` (Private)
- `GET /api/orders/myorders` (Private)
- `GET /api/orders/:id` (Private)

#### [NEW] [paymentRoutes.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/routes/paymentRoutes.js)
Exposes endpoints for payments:
- `POST /api/payment/create-checkout-session` (Private)

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/server.js)
Mount the order routes under `/api/orders` and payment routes under `/api/payment`.

