### Frontend Components

We will build the state reducer, catalog page updates, cart page, and Stripe landing pages.

#### [NEW] [CartContext.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/context/CartContext.jsx)
Manages the cart state array. Uses `useReducer` to safely update counts, add items, and empty lists.

#### [NEW] [useCart.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/hooks/useCart.js)
A simplified hook shorthand to consume the `CartContext` state.

#### [NEW] [CartPage.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/pages/CartPage.jsx)
The shopping cart checkout preparation page:
- Lists all active cart products with images, prices, subtotal calculations, and item counts.
- Displays a final subtotal summary card.
- Features a checkout button redirecting users to the Stripe Checkout page.

#### [NEW] [OrderSuccess.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/pages/OrderSuccess.jsx)
The post-checkout landing screen shown upon successful payment.

#### [NEW] [OrderFailed.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/pages/OrderFailed.jsx)
The checkout cancel/error landing screen shown when payments are canceled or fail.

#### [NEW] [Navbar.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/components/Navbar.jsx)
Refactor a global navigation header component to display the application logo, profile options, and a cart item count badge.

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/frontend/src/App.jsx)
Configure public and protected routes:
- Wrap application with `CartProvider`.
- Inject the reusable `<Navbar />` header.
- Add routes for `/cart`, `/checkout-success`, and `/checkout-failed`.

